		<content type="html" xml:base="https://skysedge.com/forum/viewtopic.php?p=192#p192"><![CDATA[
With the governor spring in hand, I was able to make a little more progress this evening!  And, I am happy to say that the dial mechanism seems to be working well.  I was concerned about trying to mate the two boards and while keeping all of the gears in place; but, they mated flawlessly (following Justine's suggestions).  Putting the bell mallet in place, however, proved to be a challenge.  I ended up loosening the one screw holding the two boards together and prying them apart slightly to help in slipping the mallet assembly into the slot.  Oh, and my hot glue didn't hold on the OLED display.  But, it seems to be coming together!  I hope it works...<dl class="file"><dt class="attach-image"><img src="https://skysedge.com/forum/download/file.php?id=4" class="postimage" alt="20230521_221723.jpg" onclick="viewableArea(this);" /></dt></dl><br /><dl class="file"><dt class="attach-image"><img src="https://skysedge.com/forum/download/file.php?id=5" class="postimage" alt="20230521_221818.jpg" onclick="viewableArea(this);" /></dt></dl><br /><dl class="file"><dt class="attach-image"><img src="https://skysedge.com/forum/download/file.php?id=6" class="postimage" alt="20230521_221826.jpg" onclick="viewableArea(this);" /></dt></dl><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://skysedge.com/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=128">rwyeth</a> — Mon May 22, 2023 3:39 am</p><hr />
